<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL POLICY ON SMOKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am a student at Chatsworth High School. I am for the ban. 
</P>
<P>
If we allow adults to smoke and not students, students will try to copy the 
adults and start smoking themselves. 
</P>
<P>
Smoking-related illnesses include heart disease, cancer, stroke and chronic 
pulmonary disease. These illnesses kill about 390,000 people each year in the 
United States. 
</P>
<P>
So why would you want to smoke? 
</P>
<P>
MARK BOLITA 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando 
</P>
</TEXT>
