<TEXT>
<P>
Newport Harbor High School scored twice in the first half and that was enough 
to hold off La Habra, 14-6, in a nonleague game Thursday night at La Habra. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor (3-1) didn't do much, however, toward derailing Jason Johnson, 
one of Orange County's leading rushers. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson gained 140 yards in 26 carries and scored the Highlanders' only 
touchdown on a 35-yard run with 8 minutes 25 seconds left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The lack of a consistent passing game offset Johnson's performance. La Habra 
(3-1) was forced to substitute Grant Mitchell at quarterback for his brother 
Greg, who injured his shoulder last week. Grant Mitchell completed only six of 
15 passes for 51 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor's two touchdowns came in a span of a little more than a minute 
in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Russell Olshefski scored on a two-yard run with 6:52 remaining to put the 
Sailors ahead, 7-0. Following an interception by Michael Stipe, the Sailors 
scored again on a 30-yard pass play from quarterback Steve Walker to tight end 
George Greenwalt. 
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the teams combined to commit 15 penalties for 137 yards. 
DENNIS KAISER 
