MORNING REPORT: MUSIC &amp; DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KGB Loses Nights at the Opera: The KGB may lose its prime seats at Moscow's 
Bolshoi Theater, a new blow to the prestige of the security agency now under 
attack as a relic of the authoritarian past. The theater's management has 
demanded closing of a "special zone" set aside for top Soviet officials and 
controlled by the KGB, the youth daily Komsomolskaya Pravda said Thursday. The 
Bolshoi's director told the newspaper removing the government boxes -- the 
former czar's loge in the center and two to one side -- would make way for 60 
additional seats. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
