<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: POLICE PROBING 3 RAPES AT USC IN LAST 10 
DAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are investigating the rapes of three USC students in the last 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
The three attacks occurred at the homes of the alleged victims near the Central 
Los Angeles campus and may have been committed by the same man, police said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
In the most recent assault, police said the attacker broke into an apartment on 
West 30th Street about 2:20 a.m. Wednesday and raped two student roommates. On 
Sept. 17, a man fitting the same general description opened a sliding glass 
door and entered a woman student's apartment on Shrine Place, police said. He 
raped the woman and stole a small amount of money. 
</P>
<P>
The man apparently was not armed during the attacks but threatened his victims 
with further injury. 
</P>
<P>
Police declined to release a detailed description of the suspect, but Police 
Cmdr. William Booth said he expected an arrest to be made soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
