<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PCP LAB EXPLODES, IGNITING HOUSE FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A PCP lab in a Windsor Hills house exploded early Thursday, ripping doors and 
windows from their casements and igniting a fire that burned the back of the 
house, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported in the 3:30 a.m. explosion in the 4900 block of 
Chesley Avenue, Sheriff's Deputy Roger Hom said. The house sustained extensive 
damage, but there was no immediate dollar estimate. 
</P>
<P>
Benny Childs Jr. 49, and Sherree McNeil, 43, were booked on suspicion of 
possession of a controled substance with intent to distribute. Sheriff's Sgt. 
Bob Olmsted said each was being held in lieu of $500,000 bond. 
</P>
</TEXT>
