<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRL, 11, ATTACKED ON WAY TO SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 11-year-old La Mesa girl was attacked and sexually assaulted on her way to 
school Thursday morning, resulting in severe bruising to her forehead and other 
injuries, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Police were looking late Thursday for a white man in his late 20s, 5-foot-11, 
180 pounds, with brown, collar-length hair. 
</P>
<P>
He was described as unshaven and wearing a pink, short-sleeved shirt, faded 
Levi's and gray and white tennis shoes, a spokeswoman for the La Mesa Police 
Department said. 
</P>
<P>
A composite drawing of the attacker has been released. The description was 
provided by the girl, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The assault occurred in an open area near Parkway Middle School at 9009 Park 
Plaza in La Mesa, the spokeswoman said. She added that the girl was struck 
several times during the attack. 
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the girl knew the attacker, Lt. Bobby Barrett said, "That 
information is not available at this time." Barrett did say the man "was 
familiar with the area." 
</P>
<P>
He said the girl was treated at a hospital. 
</P>
