<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUESTIONS ABOUT SCHOOL REFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is indeed unfortunate that The Times, even in printing a correction of 
previously published misinformation erroneously identifying one of our schools 
as the site of a shooting, continues to allude to the involvement of a school 
in the tragic death of a child. Your Sept. 13, 1990, "For the Record" article 
stated that "the suspect reportedly took the gun to school that day," and also 
that "the shooting took place after school," which are unnecessary references 
to the school in the reporting of the incident. More appropriately, the time of 
the incident should have been specified without a reference to school; and the 
alleged report that the gun was on campus is unverified and unnecessary in this 
reference by The Times. 
</P>
<P>
GEORGE J. MCKENNA III 
</P>
<P>
Superintendent of schools 
</P>
<P>
Inglewood Unified School District 
</P>
</TEXT>
