<HEADLINE>
<P>
'THE CIVIL WAR' ON HOME VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Even as "The Civil War" was unfolding on PBS this week, tapes of the 11-hour 
documentary were available on home video. 
</P>
<P>
The tapes can be obtained in a nine-cassette set through both Time-Life Video 
and PBS Video, a subsidiary of the Public Broadcasting Service. 
</P>
<P>
The Time-Life set costs $199.55 for the set, or $24.95 for each cassette. The 
PBS set is more elaborate -- including an index of people and events and a 
time-line chart -- and sells for $350 before Oct. 30 and $450 thereafter. 
</P>
<P>
Both can only be purchased by phone. Time-Life: (800) 345-8300; PBS Video (800) 
488-4727. 
</P>
