</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philadelphia 76er swingman Derek Smith will be sidelined four to six weeks 
while rehabilitating his left knee after undergoing surgery. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, 76er owner Harold Katz said he still is thinking about signing 
free agent Adrian Dantley if Smith can't play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
