</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: ROCKETS TRADE LUCAS, GET 2 HAWKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Houston Rockets traded much-traveled guard John Lucas and injured center 
Tim McCormick to the Atlanta Hawks for guards Kenny Smith and Roy Marble 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Smith, the sixth selection in the 1987 draft, was traded by the Sacramento 
Kings to Atlanta midway through last season. He averaged 11.9 points a game 
overall, but 7.7 points in 33 games with the Hawks. 
</P>
<P>
Lucas, 36, winding up his third stint with Houston, was waived twice by the 
Rockets earlier in his career after testing positive for drug use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
