<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALL-STARS FROM MAJOR SOCCER LEAGUE PLAY U.S. TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Major Soccer League, whose players complained that they were overlooked 
when the United States selected its team for last summer's World Cup, will have 
two chances this weekend to impress U.S. Coach Bob Gansler. 
</P>
<P>
The MSL All-Stars meet the national team tonight at Kansas City's Arrowhead 
Stadium and Sunday at St. Louis' Soccer Park. 
</P>
<P>
The United States has lost several starters from its World Cup team to the 
European professional leagues, but it still has both forwards, Peter Vermes and 
Bruce Murray. In a 3-0 victory over Trinidad and Tobago two weeks ago, Murray 
became the United States' all-time leading scorer with his 10th full 
international goal. 
</P>
<P>
The previous record of nine was held by midfielder Rick Davis, who will be 
playing for the MSL All-Stars. RANDY HARVEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
