<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: NEWBURY PARK; 
</P>
<P>
2 ARRESTED IN THEFTS AT HIGH SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's detectives recovered $6,400 in stolen stereo equipment and arrested 
two Newbury Park teen-agers in connection with two burglaries at the local high 
school this summer, authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The youths, ages 17 and 18, were arrested on suspicion of felony burglary 
charges, Ventura County Sheriff's Detective Joe Braga said. 
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old will be tried as a juvenile because he was 17 when the crimes 
were committed. He faces an additional charge of possession of stolen property, 
Braga said. 
</P>
<P>
In mid-June, burglars entered Newbury Park High School on Reno Road through a 
window and removed $1,400 worth of stereo speakers from the wall, Braga said. 
</P>
<P>
In mid-August, $5,000 worth of stereo equipment, including amplifiers and 
cassette decks, were taken, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Braga said the equipment was recovered Wednesday night and was returned to the 
school Thursday afternoon. KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
