<HEADLINE>
<P>
TISH JOHNSON WINS LPBT EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CLAYMONT, Del. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite missing back-to-back split conversions, Tish Johnson of Panorama City 
won her second consecutive Ladies Professional Bowlers Tour title Thursday 
night, beating Sue Neidig, 180-161, in the final of the Columbia 300 Delaware 
Open. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who earned $12,000 for the victory, won the AMF Cobra Classic last 
week. 
</P>
<P>
Kim Terrell took third with stepladder victories over Leanne Barrette, 198-179, 
and Lisa Wagner, 208-186. Terrell lost to Neidig, 201-193, to set up the final 
between top qualifier Johnson and Neidig. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
