<P>
PAYCHECK: Divorced parents who welsh on their child support may soon find it 
harder to get a loan or a credit card. . . . Credit reporting agencies have 
started logging delinquent support payments in some California counties, and 
Orange County will be included before year's end. The data comes from the 
state, which gathers it from county family support enforcement agencies. . . . 
"Pilot programs show collections increase tremendously," says a county 
administrator. . . . The flip side: If you pay on time, that's reported, too. 
