<P>
OKEFENOKEE SWAMP FIRE MUSHROOMS TO 11,000 ACRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OKEFENOKEE SWAMP, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A nearly 4-week-old fire in the Okefenokee Swamp mushroomed to 11,000 acres 
Thursday, and a spokesman for the Okefenokee Wildlife Refuge said firefighters 
abandoned the swamp to let it burn so that they could build fire lines to 
protect stands of nearby commercial pine trees. The fire was started by 
lightning Sept. 1. 
