<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
MIDWAY AIRLINES TO LAY OFF 500 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In another sign of hard times in the nation's airline industry, Midway Airlines 
said today it is cutting its staff by 10%, putting about 500 people out of 
work, and cutting service on some routes. 
</P>
<P>
"These actions are necessitated by escalating fuel costs brought on by the 
Persian Gulf crisis," Midway Chairman David Hinson said. 
</P>
<P>
All flights to Savannah, Ga., will be suspended from Nov. 1, and Midway will 
also withdraw from service eight of its least fuel-efficient aircraft. 
</P>
<P>
Midway employs about 5,700 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
