<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
STURM TO COACH U.S. VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fred Sturm of Stanford University was named the head coach of the U.S. men's 
volleyball team today. 
</P>
<P>
Sturm has coached the Cardinals since 1978 and has guided it to at least 20 
victories in each of the last six years. He was named NCAA Coach of the Year in 
1989. 
</P>
<P>
Sturm, 37, has coached a number of current Team USA players, including captain 
Scott Fortune, Jon Root and Chris Braun. A former standout at UCLA, Sturm will 
join the San Diego-based U.S. team Jan. 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
