<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
ELLIS CONVICTED OF DRUNK DRIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dale Ellis of the Seattle SuperSonics was convicted by a Seattle District Court 
jury today of drunk driving and reckless driving. 
</P>
<P>
The three-man, three-woman jury returned its verdict on the two counts after 
deliberating more than 10 hours over two days. 
</P>
<P>
Ellis, 30, denied that he was drunk when he crashed his Mercedes-Benz into a 
freeway ramp divider Jan. 12 in Seattle. He did admit having several vodka 
cocktails before the accident. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-7 Ellis, a starting guard, suffered a collapsed lung and broken 
ribs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
